---
import AboutHeroImage from '../assets/blog-placeholder-about.jpg';
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
import TerminalWindow from '../components/TerminalWindow.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About Terminote"
	description="A terminal-themed blog template for developers built with Astro"
	pubDate={new Date('February 13 2025')}
	heroImage={AboutHeroImage}
>
	<h2>What is Terminote?</h2>
	<p>
		Terminote is a <strong>terminal-themed blog template</strong> designed for developers who want a unique,
		distraction-free writing experience. Inspired by the aesthetic of macOS Terminal, it combines the
		familiarity of command-line interfaces with the power of modern web technologies.
	</p>
	<p>
		Whether you're documenting your coding journey, sharing technical tutorials, or building a personal
		brand, Terminote provides a beautiful, fast, and fully customizable foundation that stands out from
		traditional blog designs.
	</p>

	<h2>Features</h2>
	
	<h3>üé® 4 Beautiful Terminal Themes</h3>
	<p>
		Switch between four carefully crafted color schemes that capture different terminal aesthetics:
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Pro</strong> - Default macOS Terminal dark theme with blue accents</li>
		<li><strong>Homebrew</strong> - Matrix-inspired green terminal with neon glow</li>
		<li><strong>Nocturnal</strong> - Cyberpunk purple and cyan for night owls</li>
		<li><strong>Retro</strong> - Vintage amber monitor aesthetic</li>
	</ul>

	<TerminalWindow title="terminote-themes" showStatusBar={true} statusText="zsh">
		<div class="terminal-content">
			<div class="command-line">
				<span class="prompt">‚ûú</span>
				<span class="command">terminote theme set pro</span>
			</div>
			<div class="output">
				Theme switched to: Pro (Default macOS Terminal)
			</div>
			
			<div class="command-line">
				<span class="prompt">‚ûú</span>
				<span class="command">terminote theme set homebrew</span>
			</div>
			<div class="output">
				Theme switched to: Homebrew (Matrix Green)
			</div>
			
			<div class="command-line">
				<span class="prompt">‚ûú</span>
				<span class="command">_</span>
			</div>
		</div>
	</TerminalWindow>

	<h3>‚ú® Authentic Terminal UI</h3>
	<p>
		Experience blogging with authentic terminal aesthetics including:
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li>macOS-style traffic light buttons (close, minimize, maximize)</li>
		<li>Blinking cursor animation</li>
		<li>Subtle scanline overlay effect</li>
		<li>Command prompt styling (user@terminote:~$)</li>
		<li>Terminal window frames with shadows</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>‚ö° Lightning Fast Performance</h3>
	<p>
		Built with <a href="https://astro.build/" target="_blank">Astro</a>, Terminote ships with zero JavaScript
		by default, resulting in exceptional performance metrics:
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li>100/100 Lighthouse Performance score</li>
		<li>Instant page loads with static generation</li>
		<li>Optimized images with Sharp</li>
		<li>Minimal CSS with theme variables</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>üì± Optimized for 2K Displays</h3>
	<p>
		Every element is scaled to 150% for perfect visibility on high-resolution displays:
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Base font size: 24px (up from 16px)</li>
		<li>Container width: 1350px (up from 900px)</li>
		<li>Traffic lights: 18px (up from 12px)</li>
		<li>Touch-friendly buttons and links</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>For Developers</h2>
	
	<h3>üõ†Ô∏è Tech Stack</h3>
	<p>Terminote is built with modern, developer-friendly technologies:</p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Astro 5.x</strong> - All-in-one web framework</li>
		<li><strong>TypeScript</strong> - Type-safe code</li>
		<li><strong>Zod</strong> - Schema validation for content</li>
		<li><strong>MDX</strong> - Markdown with JSX components</li>
		<li><strong>Sharp</strong> - Image optimization</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>üìù Content Collections</h3>
	<p>
		Terminote uses Astro's Content Collections with Zod schemas for type-safe blog posts. Simply add
		Markdown or MDX files to <code>src/content/blog/</code>:
	</p>

	<TerminalWindow title="content/blog/my-post.md" showStatusBar={true} statusText="markdown">
		<div class="terminal-content">
			<div class="code-block">
---
title: 'My Awesome Post'
description: 'A detailed description'
pubDate: 2025-02-13
heroImage: '../../assets/blog-placeholder-1.jpg'
---

# My Awesome Post

Write your content here using **Markdown** syntax.
			</div>
		</div>
	</TerminalWindow>

	<h3>üé® Customizing Themes</h3>
	<p>
		Creating custom themes is straightforward. Add a new CSS file in <code>src/styles/themes/</code>:
	</p>

	<TerminalWindow title="styles/themes/custom.css" showStatusBar={true} statusText="css">
		<div class="terminal-content">
			<pre class="code-block">[data-theme="custom"] {'{'}
  --terminal-bg: #0a0a0f;
  --terminal-text: #00ff88;
  --terminal-accent: #00ff88;
  --terminal-success: #00ff88;
  --terminal-cyan: #00ffff;
  --terminal-magenta: #ff00ff;
{'}'}</pre>
		</div>
	</TerminalWindow>

	<h3>üîç SEO & Meta</h3>
	<p>Terminote includes built-in SEO features:</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Auto-generated RSS feed at <code>/rss.xml</code></li>
		<li>Sitemap generation</li>
		<li>OpenGraph and Twitter Card meta tags</li>
		<li>Canonical URLs</li>
		<li>Structured data support</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Getting Started</h2>
	<p>Ready to start your terminal blog? Here's how to get up and running in minutes:</p>

	<TerminalWindow title="terminal" showStatusBar={true} statusText="bash">
		<div class="terminal-content">
			<div class="command-line">
				<span class="prompt">$</span>
				<span class="command">git clone https://github.com/gnokit/terminote.git</span>
			</div>
			<div class="command-line">
				<span class="prompt">$</span>
				<span class="command">cd terminote</span>
			</div>
			<div class="command-line">
				<span class="prompt">$</span>
				<span class="command">npm install</span>
			</div>
			<div class="command-line">
				<span class="prompt">$</span>
				<span class="command">npm run dev</span>
			</div>
			<div class="output success">
				ready in 350ms
				
				  üöÄ Local: http://localhost:4321/
				  ‚≠ê Terminote is running!
			</div>
		</div>
	</TerminalWindow>

	<h2>Author</h2>
	<p>
		Terminote was created by <strong>Paul Chan</strong> (<a href="https://github.com/gnokit" target="_blank">@gnokit</a>).
		It's open source and available on <a href="https://github.com/gnokit/terminote" target="_blank">GitHub</a>.
	</p>
	<p>
		Feel free to fork, customize, and make it your own. If you build something cool with Terminote,
		I'd love to hear about it!
	</p>
</Layout>

<style>
	.terminal-content {
		font-family: "SF Mono", "Menlo", "Monaco", "Courier New", monospace;
		line-height: 1.8;
	}

	.command-line {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 12px;
		margin: 4px 0;
	}

	.command-line .prompt {
		color: var(--terminal-accent);
		font-weight: 600;
	}

	.command-line .command {
		color: var(--terminal-text);
	}

	.output {
		color: var(--terminal-text-muted);
		margin: 4px 0 12px 24px;
		white-space: pre-line;
	}

	.output.success {
		color: var(--terminal-success);
	}

	.code-block {
		color: var(--terminal-cyan);
		white-space: pre;
		overflow-x: auto;
	}
</style>
